1. Generate line table
   text_playback/*.csv
   → line_table.csv

2. Generate or update qualitative codebook
   personality_qualitative_code_log.csv
   → codebook_used.csv

3. Qualitative-code each line
   line_table.csv + codebook_used.csv
   → line_code_assignments.csv

4. Build ENA wide extract
   line_table.csv + line_code_assignments.csv
   → ena_wide.csv / ena_wide.rds

5. Run rENA
   ena_wide.rds
   → ENA model, plots, lineweights

   Important distinction:

The v1 direct converter does not perform qualitative coding. It only prepares line-level replay data, reads an existing line-code assignment file, pivots that assignment file wide, and writes ENA-ready outputs.

A separate coding script is required to generate line_code_assignments.csv from line_table.csv and the qualitative codebook.